3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHopping%20on%20to%20the%20turbocharged%20rally%20that%20began%20in%20October%2C%20retail%20investors%20have%20been%20steadily%20snapping%20up%20more%20stocks.%20Daily%20net%20purchases%20hit%20a%20year-to-date%20peak%20in%20early%20February%20at%20%241.5%20billion%20across%20equities%2C%20and%20total%20trading%20volume%20has%20tripled%20since%20pre-COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20though%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-record-highs-investors-finance-wall-street-2024-2%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20breaking%20new%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20sugar-rush%20rally%20is%20a%20marked%20reversal%20from%20anemic%202022%20and%20wobbly%202023%2C%20the%20cohort%20of%20investors%20are%20more%20measured%20in%20their%20enthusiasm%20lately.%20The%20total%20volume%20traded%20is%20below%20trends%20of%20the%20previous%20bull%20market%20rallies%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F9qbN7%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20aggregate%20monthly%20trading%20flows%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20like%20they%20want%20to%20participate%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20miss%20out%20on%20the%20rally%20too%20much%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20doing%20it%20mainly%20by%20the%20bigger%20names%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Marco%20Lachini%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20Vanda%20Research%2C%20which%20tracks%20retail%20trader%20activity%20across%20stocks%20and%20ETFs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20they're%20using%20SPY%20or%20QQQ%20instead%20of%20the%20triple%20QQQ%20or%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20heavy%20usage%20of%20leveraged%20ETFs%20in%202021%20that%20has%20diminished%20significantly%20after%20they%20got%20burned%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20popular%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20Nasdaq%20100%20ETFs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20meme-stock%20era%2C%20retail%20investors%20were%20lapping%20up%20shares%20of%20things%20like%20leveraged%20ETFs%2C%20which%20amplify%20the%20returns%20and%20the%20losses%20of%20the%20underlying%20assets%20they%20track.%20They%20loved%20small%20companies%20that%20didn't%20need%20to%20have%20rock-solid%20balance%20sheets%2C%20like%20GameStop%20and%20AMC.%20They%20were%20also%20big%20on%20squeezing%20stocks%20in%20what%20seemed%20like%20a%20David-and-Goliath%20fight%20against%20short%20sellers%20on%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20market%20tanked%20in%202022.%20Faithful%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bdiamond%20hands%26quot%3B%20never-sell%20mantra%2C%20retail%20traders%20stuck%20it%20out%20and%20saw%20the%20value%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2022-12-09%2Fretail-traders-lose-350-billion-in-brutal-year-for-taking-risks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eportfolios%20shrivel%20by%20around%2030%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20unhinged%20speculative%20frenzy%20has%20tapered.%20For%20one%2C%20hedge%20funds%20have%20become%20smarter%20at%20anticipating%20attempts%20to%20squeeze%20stocks%2C%20but%20retail%20investors%20have%20also%20matured.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20reason%20why%20trading%20activity%20hasn't%20touched%20the%202021%20levels%20is%20because%20the%20memory%20of%20being%20burned%20in%202022%20is%20too%20fresh%2C%20Lachini%20explained.%20As%20retail%20investor%20portfolios%20have%20finally%20caught%20up%20with%20the%20all-time%20highs%2C%20they're%20not%20big%20on%20making%20big%20YOLO%20bets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20having%20jumped%20into%20the%20latest%20bull%20market%20rally%20right%20on%20time%2C%20there's%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.bus