0Devices%2C%20and%20the%20QQQ%20were%20in%20the%20top%20five%20shares%20that%20saw%20the%20largest%20net%20inflows%20in%20the%20past%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FCG9kP%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Net%20purchases%20of%20AI-related%20stocks%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20see%20month%20to%20month%20is%20that%20what%20goes%20down%2C%20our%20customers%20buy%20a%20little%20more%20of%2C%20and%20what%20goes%20up%20a%20lot%2C%20they%20trim%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Steph%20Guild%2C%20head%20of%20investment%20strategy%20at%20Robinhood%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20patterns%20mimic%20that%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20investor%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20wasn't%20exactly%20a%20part%20of%20their%20brand%20before.%20They%20are%20also%20exploring%20different%20themes%20beyond%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fus-tech-stocks-spx-forecast-nvidia-meta-magnificent-seven-label-2024-2%5C%22%3Eproverbial%20Magnificent%207%20trade.%3C%2Fa%3E%20They've%20been%20dipping%20into%20healthcare%2C%20financial%20tech%2C%20and%20even%20cruise%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20seeing%20more%20diversification%20in%20what's%20owned%20in%20portfolios%2C%20generally%20speaking%2C%20than%20let's%20say%20two%20years%20ago%20or%20three%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Guild%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20as%20socially%20fueled.%20While%20there%20is%20discourse%20on%20social%20media%20obviously%20about%20this%2C%20it's%20not%20like%20necessarily%20everybody's%20piling%20into%20one%20name%20or%20two%20names.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20they%20are%20feeling%20pretty%20good%20about%20their%20choices.%20According%20to%20a%20recent%20Charles%20Schwab%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpressroom.aboutschwab.com%2Fpress-releases%2Fpress-release%2F2024%2FSchwab-Survey-Bullish-Sentiment-Surges-Among-Retail-Traders%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%3Epoll%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20traders'%20confidence%20in%20their%20own%20decision-making%20hit%20the%20highest%20level%20in%20survey%20history%20at%2068%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-rally-nvidia-ai-retail-investors-meme-stocks-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709386201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1fe146080194819fb9d9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-rally-nvidia-ai-retail-investors-meme-stocks-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Net%20purchases%20of%20equities%20by%20retail%20investors%20hit%20a%20year-to-date%20peak%20in%20February%2C%20but%20trading%20volumes%20are%20below%20trend%20compared%20to%20other%20recent%20rallies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asoni%40insider.com%20(Aruni%20Soni)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-rally-nvidia-ai-retail-investors-meme-stocks-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Interview%20%7C%20In%20Search%20of%20Forgotten%20Rice%3A%20The%20Experience%20of%20Bengal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02173951%2FUntitled-design-24.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20rice%20conservator%20credited%20with%20conserving%20400%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%20over%20his%20three-decades-long%20career%2C%20Anupam%20Paul%20states%20that%20these%20indigenous%20rice%20species%20are%20hardy%20and%20more%20suited%20to%20a%20changing%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%201970s%2C%20India%20has%20lost%20more%20than%20a%20lakh%20varieties%20of%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20that%20were%20consumed%20before%20the%20Green%20Revolution.%20With%20the%20government%20subsidising%20a%20few%20high-yielding%20varieties%20that%20provided%20abundant%20grains%20on%20applying%20chemical%20fertilisers%2C%20the%20promotion%20of%20monoculture%20caused%20a%20massive%20loss%20of%20species%20and%20crop%20diversity.%20India%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20are%20those%20landraces%20that%20have%20adapted%20to%20local%20climatic%20and%20ecological%20conditions%20and%20are%20cultivated%20and%20multiplied%20by%20farmers%20for%20at%20least%20the%20last%20half%20a%20century.%20Ninety%20percent%20of%20these%20varieties%20are%20estimated%20to%20be%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnupam%20Paul%2C%20a%20passionate%20seed%20conservator%2C%20who%20retired%20as%20the%20Assistant%20Director%20in%20the%20Nadia-based%20Agricultural%20Training%20Centre%2C%20Bengal%20government%2C%20is%20credited%20with%20conserving%20more%20than%20400%20varieties%20of%20traditional%20rice%20seeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Anumeha%20Yadav%2C%C2%A0Paul%20stated%20that%20as%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20make%20temperatures%20and%20rainfall%20more%20erratic%2C%20and%20lead%20to%20breeding%20new%20pests%20and%20diseases%2C%20chemically%20grown%20varieties%20will%20be%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20fungi%20attacks%20or%20reduced%20efficacy%20of%20pesticides%2C%20making%20the%20remaining%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%20a%20precious%20genetic%20and%20cultural%20inheritance%20to%20protect%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20you%20first%20start%20focusing%20on%20conserving%20the%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20retired%20from%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20West%20Bengal%20as%20the%20Additional%20Director%20of%20Agriculture%20(Personnel)%20in%20February%202023%2C%20after%20working%20in%20the%20government%20for%2031%20years.%20While%20I%20was%20still%20in%20government%20service%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20folk%20rice%20collection%2C%20conservation%2C%20popularization%20and%20organic%20farming%20in%20the%20Biodiversity%20Conservation%20Farm%20of%20Agricultural%20Training%20Centre%2C%20in%20Fulia%2C%20in%20Nadia%20district%20under%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Agriculture%20in%20eastern%20Bengal%20for%2020%20years.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20I%20collected%20more%20than%20400%20folk%20rice%20varieties%20from%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014-15%2C%20a%20scheme%20named%20Rastriya%20Krishi%20Vikas%20Yojona(RKVY)%20on%20indigenous%20or%20folk%20rice%20varieties%E2%80%99%20collection%2C%20conservation%2C%20popularization%20and%20value%20addition%20was%20implemented%20for%20five%20years%20in%20Bengal%2C%20first%20in%2011%20districts%20then%20expanded%20to%2016%20districts.%20This%20was%20a%20unique%20venture.%C2%A0%20The%20agriculture%20department%20demonstrated%20the%20amazing%20potential%20of%20Desi%20High%20Yielding%20folk%20rice%20varieties%20that%20can%20compete%20with%20the%20modern%20varieties%20to%20farmers.%20We%20showed%20that%20indigenous%20rice%20varieties%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Kerala%20Sundari%2C%20Bahurupi%2C%20can%20give%20a%20good%20yield%20of%20six%20tonnes%20per%20hectare%20when%20cultivated%20under%20organic%20mode.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20of%20such%20attempts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174417%2FPanicles-.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174417%2FPanicles-.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174417%2FPanicles--300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174417%2FPanicles--1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699790%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETraditional%20rice%20panicles.%20Photo%3A%20Anupam%20Paul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20now%20more%20than%2040%20farmers%E2%80%99%20groups%2C%20each%20with%2020%20to%2030%20farmer%20families%20and%20numerous%20individual%20farmers%20in%20various%20districts%20who%20have%20re-adopted%20folk%20rice%20replacing%20modern%20varieties%20under%20chemical%20mode%20and%20its%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20is%20less%20than%20modern%20varieties.%20It%20is%20nutritious%20and%20tasty.%20Now%2C%20more%20than%20400%20folk%20rice%20varieties%20are%20being%20cultivated%20in%20selected%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20across%20Bengal%3B%20some%20farmers%20are%20cultivating%20five%20to%20six%20folk%20varieties%20in%20large%20areas%20for%20commercial%20purposes%2C%20such%20as%20Bahurup%2C%20Govindbhog%2C%20Kalabhat%2C%20Baspur%20rice%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMainstream%20agricultural%20courses%20in%20our%20universities%20teach%20chemical%20farming%20and%20during%20my%20study%20I%20was%20trained%20in%20the%20same.%20In%202000%2C%20while%20working%20as%20an%20agriculture%20officer%2C%20I%20happened%20to%20read%20a%20book%20in%20Bengali%20called%20%3Cem%3ELoot%20Hoye%20Jai%20Swadeshbhum%3C%2Fem%3Ei%20(%E2%80%98My%20Homeland%20is%20Plundered%E2%80%99)%C2%A0%20by%20plant%20scientist%20Debal%20Deb%2C%20who%20now%20runs%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20seeds%20bank%20in%20Asia%20conserving%20more%20than%201%2C400%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20varieties%20in%20Odisha.%20This%20book%20was%20about%20food%20politics%2C%20how%20yield%20potentialities%20of%20folk%20rice%20have%20been%20suppressed%2C%20a%20story%20of%20our%20society%20ignoring%20the%20nutrition%20of%20folk%20rice%2C%20and%20the%20total%20crop%20productivity%20of%20our%20rice%20ecosystem.%20Deb%E2%80%99s%20book%20revealed%20a%20different%20story%20from%20what%20I%20had%20known%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20you%20trace%20and%20explain%20how%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20affected%20cultivation%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20was%20launched%20in%20the%201960s%20under%20the%20perceived%20threat%20of%20shortages%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20to%20feed%20the%20increasing%20population%20and%20it%20was%20based%20on%20promoting%20primarily%20monoculture%20of%20rice%20and%20wheat.%C2%A0%20During%20this%20so-called%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20our%20vast%20traditional%20area%20of%20rain-fed%20farming%20in%20drought%20prone%20areas%20growing%20ecologically%20more%20suitable%20cereals%20such%20as%20millet%20and%20traditional%20maize%20were%20ignored.%20Rice%20and%20wheat%20varieties%20were%20developed%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20they%20could%20tolerate%20large%20amounts%20of%20fertilizers.%20Owing%20to%20application%20of%20chemical%20fertilizers%20especially%20nitrogenous%20fertilizers%2C%20the%20crop%20become%20susceptible%20and%20prone%20to%20pest%20attack%2C%20so%20pesticide%20use%20increases.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20millet%20crops%20are%20hardy%3B%20do%20not%20require%20external%20inputs%20such%20as%20chemical%20fertilizer%2C%20and%20pesticides.%20It%20does%20not%20require%20a%20vast%20tract%20of%20irrigated%20land.%C2%A0%20But%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20chemical%20intensive%20agriculture%20was%20to%20externalize%20the%20agricultural%20inputs%2C%20they%20resulted%20in%20making%20us%20deeply%20dependent%20on%20these%20inputs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMassive%20propaganda%20promoting%20chemical%20farming%20with%20monoculture%20pushed%20back%20the%20task%20of%20research%20in%20and%20promotion%20of%20our%20own%20high%20yielding%20Traditional%20Rice%20Varieties.%20Dr.%20R%20H%20Richharia%2C%20the%20famous%20rice%20scientist%2C%20the%20former%20Director%20of%20Central%20Rice%20Research%20Institute%2C%20Cuttack%2C%20was%20sceptical%20of%20japonica%20varieties%20being%20imported%20in%20India%20without%20plant%20quarantine%20as%20it%20would%20bring%20rice%20disease%20and%20pests%20of%20Japan.%20He%20had%20selected%20some%20of%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20having%20yield%20potential%20of%205-7%20tonnes%20per%20hectare.%20But%20he%20was%20dismissed%20from%20service%20(he%20served%20from%201959%20to%201966)%20in%201966%20without%20assigning%20any%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMainstream%20media%20campaign%20aggressively%20pushed%20chemical%20intensive%20farming%20on%20ordinary%20farmers.%20Farmers%20slowly%20moved%20away%20from%20and%20forgot%20the%20benefits%20of%20folk%20rice%20like%20its%20low%20cost%20of%20cultivation%2C%20nutritive%20qualities%2C%20adaptability%20in%20marginal%20lands%2C%20economically%20and%20ecologically%20profitable%20fish-cum-paddy%20culture%20that%20is%20possible%20in%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice.%20Only%20the%20concept%20of%20low%20grain%20yield%20was%20pushed%20and%20acquired%20center-stage%20in%20all%20discussion%20and%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20yield%20of%20modern%20varieties%20declines%20after%20some%20years%2C%20until%20a%20new%20modern%20rice%20variety%20comes%20into%20the%20market%20requiring%20more%20and%20more%20chemical%20fertilizers.%20For%20example%2C%20in%201975%2C%20one%20kilo%20of%20nitrogen%2C%20phosphate%20and%20potassium%20fertilizer%20roughly%20gave%2015%20kilo%20grains%3B%20now%20it%20is%20the%20reverse%3A%20Farmers%20are%20using%20nearly15%20kilo%20of%20chemical%20fertilizers%20to%20get%201%20kilo%20of%20food%20grain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20intention%20of%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20was%20to%20introduce%20farming%20with%20chemicals%20and%20fertilizer%20responsive%20modern%20varieties.%20But%20the%20traditional%20varieties%20do%20not%20require%20chemical%20fertilizers%20and%20pesticides%20the%20same%20way%2C%20and%20the%20seeds%20can%20be%20used%20for%20years%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20been%20the%20impact%20of%20all%20this%20on%20crops%2C%20and%20on%20biodiversity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20one%20of%20the%2017%20mega%20diverse%20countries%20rich%20in%20flora%20and%20fauna%20including%20crop%20diversity.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Plant%20Genetic%20Resources%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20India%20had%2082%2C000%20rice%2C%2038000%20wheat%2C%2010000%20pigeon%20pea%2C%2016000%20gram%2C%C2%A0%203668%20brinjal%2C%2046000%20various%20millets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20colossal%20loss%20of%20our%20crop%20biodiversity%20that%20is%20the%20key%20to%20our%20future%20food%20security.%20Surprisingly%2C%20this%20fact%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20mention%20in%20any%20of%20our%20textbooks.%20Now%2C%20we%20may%20not%20find%20even%202%2C000%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20in%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20of%20India.%20Researchers%20found%20that%20more%20than%2098%20percent%20of%20those%20varieties%20have%20been%20extinct%20from%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174914%2FUntitled-design-25-1-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174914%2FUntitled-design-25-1-1.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174914%2FUntitled-design-25-1-1-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02174914%2FUntitled-design-25-1-1-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699791%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentational%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Anupam%20Paul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20extinct%20rice%20varieties%20of%20Bengal%2C%20for%20example%2C%20are%20Pabashi%2C%20Kachanani%2C%20Hatirdani%2C%20Choto%20Josowa%2C%20Guligati%2C%20etc.%20The%20variety%20Guligati%2C%20deep-water%20summer%20rice%20%E2%80%93%20which%20can%20withstand%20stagnant%20water%20of%201%20feet%20and%20above%2C%20over%2025-30%20days%20and%20is%20harvested%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20of%20South%2024%20Parganas%20was%20last%20documented%20in%201998.%20So%2C%20it%20has%20been%20lost%20for%20future%20generations.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20such%20modern%20variety%20for%20deep%20water%20during%20Boro%2C%20or%20the%20summer%20rice%20period.%20Practically%2C%20no%20scientist%20can%20bring%20them%20back%20even%20if%20we%20can%20send%20the%20Moon%20Missions%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20do%20you%20believe%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20conserve%20such%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20quite%20natural%20some%20crop%20varieties%20may%20be%20extinct%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%20due%20to%20non-cultivation%20or%20any%20weather%20aberration.%20Our%20forefathers%20meticulously%20selected%20and%20nurtured%20some%20of%20these%20varieties%20for%20future%20generations.%20Yet%2C%20modern%20policy%20makers%20are%20not%20documenting%20the%20traditional%20varieties%E2%80%99%20features%20of%20nutrition%2C%20yield%20per%20litre%20of%20water%2C%20richness%20of%20iron%2C%20zinc%20and%20antioxidants%2C%20grain%20and%20straw%20yield%2C%20ability%20to%20adapt%20in%20marginal%20lands%20and%20lastly%20the%20grain%20yield.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditional%20rice%20varieties%20are%20the%20basis%20of%20future%20food%20security.%20We%20now%20need%20crop%20diversity%20more%20than%20ever%20as%20it%20also%20provides%20food%20security%20against%20natural%20calamities%2C%20as%20we%20witnessed%20during%20cyclonic%20storm%20Aila%20in%202009%20in%20Sundarbans%20areas%20in%20saline%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENutritious%20qualities%20of%20folk%20rice%20are%20still%20being%20fully%20analysed.%20But%20those%20that%20have%20been%20analysed%20so%20far%20have%20qualities%20that%20ought%20to%20make%20us%20take%20notice%20and%20pay%20attention%20to%20them.%20Many%20of%20these%20varieties%20are%20rich%20in%20anti-oxidants%2C%20beta%20carotene%20%E2%80%93%20precursor%20of%20Vitamin%20A%2C%20and%20cancer%20preventive%20anthocyanin%20particularly%20in%20red%20and%20black%20rice%20varieties.%20Unpolished%20rice%20is%20good%20for%20diabetes%2C%20for%20lactating%20mothers.%20are%20full%20of%20essential%20micronutrient%20minerals%2C%20such%20as%20iron%20and%20zinc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20role%20can%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%20play%20as%20society%20grapples%20with%20climate%20change%3F%20How%20are%20they%20more%20suitable%20to%20climate%20change%20and%20local%20agro-ecology%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%20are%20suitable%20for%20marginal%20lands%20like%20drought%2C%20flood%2C%20saline-prone%20areas.%20Some%20pre-Kharif%20rice(called%20Aus)%20rice%20varieties%20sown%20in%20the%20month%20of%20May-%20June%20can%20withstand%20high%20temperature%20and%20moisture%20stress%20in%20the%20soil.%20Some%20varieties%20can%20withstand%20drought%20at%20initial%20phase%20and%20flood%20at%20later%20stage.%20Daseriya%20rice%20of%20Bihar%20has%20this%20unique%20feature.%20Everywhere%2C%20we%20are%20experiencing%20climatic%20aberrations%3B%20rainfall%20is%20not%20evenly%20distributed%2C%20erratic%20and%20scanty%2C%20not%20suitable%20for%20Kharif%20rice%20(planted%20June%20to%20November).%C2%A0%20Traditional%20varieties%20of%20Aus%20rice%20can%20cope%20with%20this%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20Aila%20cyclones%20in%202009%20in%20Sundarbans%20areas%20in%20saline%20zones%2C%20most%20of%20cases%20all%20the%20so-called%20modern%20salt-tolerant%20rice%20varieties%20failed%20while%20the%20traditional%20salt%20tolerant%20varieties%20withstood%20the%20climatic%20vagaries.%20These%20are%20low%20yielding%2C%20but%20tolerate%20substantial%20salt%20whereas%20modern%20salt-tolerant%20varieties%20can%20give%20high%20yield%20in%20comparatively%20less%20salt%20affected%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%20in%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20suitable%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20for%20marginal%20lands%20like%20deep%20water%20paddy%2C%20salt%20tolerant%20paddy%2C%20both%20drought%20and%20flood%20tolerant%20paddy%2C%20drought%20tolerant%20paddy%2C%20paddy%20for%20broadcasting%20in%20upland%20have%20declined%20significantly.%20West%20Bengal%20had%20more%20than%205%2C000%20folk%20rice%3B%20apart%20from%20conservation%20plots%2C%20but%20we%20may%20find%20hardly%20150%20varieties%20in%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20now.%20Sadly%2C%20despite%20research%2C%20no%20modern%20rice%20variety%20can%20replace%20them%20or%20a%20match%20for%20them.%20No%20crops%20(be%20it%20hybrids%2C%20or%20Genetically%20Modified%20crops)%20in%20the%20world%20will%20be%20able%20to%20withstand%20extreme%20climate%20aberration%20that%20we%20are%20approaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModern%20varieties%2C%20the%20High%20Yielding%20Varieties(HYVs)%2C%20are%20designed%20so%20selfishly%20that%20its%20grain%20is%20meant%20only%20for%20humans.%20But%20in%20India%2C%20paddy%20straw%20is%20the%20main%20fodder%20for%20cattle%20and%20bullocks.%20But%20HYV%20of%20rice%20provides%20meagre%20fodder%2C%20and%20cattle%20do%20not%20eat%20it.%20The%20straw%20is%20not%20suitable%20for%20thatching%2C%20packing%20and%20mushroom%20production.%C2%A0%20The%20traditional%20varieties%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20provide%20adequate%20straw%20as%20fodder%2C%20mushrooms%20grow%20easily%20on%20the%20paddy%20straw%20in%20the%20monsoon%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnumeha%20Yadav%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20focusing%20on%20labour%20and%20rural%20policy%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709386143000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02173951%2FUntitled-design-24.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Finterview-in-search-of-forgotten-rice-the-experience-of-bengal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anupam%20Paul%2C%20a%20passionate%20seed%20conservator%2C%20who%20retired%20as%20the%20Assistant%20Director%20in%20the%20Nadia-based%20Agricultural%20Training%20Centre%2C%20Bengal%20government%2C%20is%20credited%20with%20conserving%20more%20than%20400%20varieties%20of%20traditional%20rice%20seeds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Finterview-in-search-of-forgotten-rice-the-experience-of-bengal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20upgrades%20that%20are%20always%20worth%20the%20money%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20who's%20been%20on%2050%20cruises%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22megan%20posing%20for%20a%20photo%20on%20the%20icon%20of%20the%20seas%20cruise%20ship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df49e76080194819fac230%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20go%20on%20multiple%20cruises%20a%20year.%20%3Cp%3EMegan%20duBois%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-i-never-buy-on-a-cruise-frequent-traveler-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaking%2050%20cruises%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I've%20learned%20that%20some%20upgrades%20are%20worth%20the%20hype.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20always%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-rooms-windows-balconies-not-worth-it-frequent-cruiser-2024%5C%22