law%20hasn't%20passed%20yet%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20what%20I'll%20be%20doing.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20data-pm-slice%3D%5C%221%201%20%5B%5D%5C%22%3EAs%20I'm%20starting%20the%20process%20of%20filing%20my%20taxes%20for%202023%2C%20I'm%20realizing%20that%20this%20return%20will%20look%20a%20lot%20different%20from%20years%20past.%20Not%20only%20is%20this%20the%20first%20year%20that%20I'm%20filing%20jointly%20with%20my%20husband%2C%20but%20we%20just%20had%20a%20baby.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffederal-income-tax-calculator%5C%22%3Etax%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20pretty%20straightforward.%20But%20this%20time%2C%20we're%20finding%20ourselves%20looking%20up%20different%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftax-credit-vs-tax-deduction%5C%22%3Edeductions%20and%20credits%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20we're%20eligible%20for%20as%20first-time%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20certified%20public%20accountant%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cpafirmnyc.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaul%20Miller%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20and%20how%20the%20proposed%20changes%20could%20impact%202023%20tax%20returns.%20Here's%20what%20he%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20You're%20eligible%20for%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20until%20your%20child%20is%2017%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20much%20about%20the%20current%20child%20tax%20credit%20and%20asked%20Miller%20if%20I%20was%20eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20child%20under%20the%20age%20of%2017%2C%20you%20could%20qualify%20to%20receive%20a%20child%20tax%20credit%20on%20your%20tax%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20Miller%20said%20that%20the%20tax%20credit%20is%20up%20to%20%242%2C000%20per%20child%20that%20qualifies%2C%20as%20long%20as%20your%20annual%20income%20is%20not%20more%20than%20%24200%2C000%20for%20a%20single%20taxpayer%20and%20%24400%2C000%20for%20couples%20filing%20jointly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IRS%20lists%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fcredits-deductions%2Findividuals%2Fchild-tax-credit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequirements%20for%20eligibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20website.%20Since%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20earn%20less%20than%20%24400%2C000%20in%20modified%20adjusted%20gross%20income%20and%20our%20child%20is%20under%20a%20year%20old%2C%20we%20should%20receive%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20on%20our%202023%20tax%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20said%20that%20the%20biggest%20benefit%20of%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20is%20that%20it%20saves%20a%20family%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%2C%20you're%20getting%20a%20dollar-for-dollar%20credit%20against%20your%20taxes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BKids%20cost%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20The%20government%20wants%20to%20encourage%20families%20to%20have%20children%2C%20and%20this%20credit%20is%20a%20way%20to%20give%20you%20%242%2C000%20to%20offset%20your%20expenses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20The%20new%20child%20tax%20credit%20comes%20with%20a%20few%20big%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20January%2C%20the%20House%20approved%20a%20bill%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenhanced-child-tax-credit-parents-passes-house-business-tax-relief-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETax%20Relief%20for%20American%20Families%20and%20Workers%20Act%20of%202024%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Inside%20the%20bill%20was%20an%20update%20to%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20in%20two%20big%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Miller%20shared%20that%20the%20new%20child%20tax%20credit%20could%20change%20how%20much%20families%20would%20get%20back%20on%20their%20tax%20refund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20Miller%20said%20that%20if%20you%20don't%20owe%20taxes%2C%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20would%20provide%20you%20with%20%241%2C600%20back%20in%20your%20annual%20tax%20refund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20proposed%20bill%2C%20a%20family%20would%20receive%20%241%2C800%20in%202023%2C%20%241%2C900%20in%202024%2C%20and%20%242%2C000%20in%202025%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Miller%20said%20that%20the%20biggest%20amendment%20to%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20under%20this%20new%20bill%20would%20be%20how%20it%20allows%20people%20who%20earn%20less%20money%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20the%20credit%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20a%20filer%20must%20earn%20at%20least%20%242%2C500%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnder%20the%20new%20bill%2C%20people%20can%20opt%20to%20use%20earned%20income%20from%20the%20current%20year%20or%20prior%20year%20to%20meet%20the%20requirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20shared%20how%20significant%20this%20could%20be%20for%20low-income%20families%20who%20otherwise%20would%20miss%20out%20on%20receiving%20this%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20It's%20OK%20if%20you%20already%20filed%20your%20taxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%20the%20new%20tax%20bill%20is%20waiting%20for%20a%20Senate%20vote%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20definitive%20date%20on%20when%20that%20will%20take%20place.%20But%20since%20the%20deadline%20to%20file%202023%20taxes%20is%20April%2015%2C%20some%20people%20have%20already%20filed%20their%20taxes.%20If%20the%20new%20tax%20deal%20is%20passed%20by%20the%20Senate%2C%20Miller%20said%20those%20who%20already%20filed%20will%20still%20benefit%20from%20the%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20these%20new%20tax%20changes%20pass%20in%20the%20senate%2C%20my%20assumption%20is%20that%20the%20IRS%20will%20adjust%20the%20return%20for%20those%20who%20filed%20already%20and%20send%20them%20the%20u