750%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20military%20action%20began%20after%20Hamas%20launched%20attacks%20into%20Israel%20that%20killed%20more%20killed%20more%20than%201%2C200%20people%2C%20with%20240%20others%20taken%20as%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20death%20toll%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20five-month-long%20military%20campaign%20in%20Gaza%20now%20stands%20at%20over%2030%2C000%2C%20with%20more%20than%2071%2C000%20wounded.%20The%20US%20secretary%20of%20defence%20Lloyd%20Austin%20said%20at%20a%20Congressional%20hearing%20that%20around%2025%2C000%20women%20and%20children%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20since%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20backlash%20from%20European%20capitals%20after%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20killing%20has%20been%20sharp%2C%20with%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20squarely%20blaming%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDeep%20indignation%20at%20the%20images%20coming%20from%20Gaza%20where%20civilians%20have%20been%20targeted%20by%20Israeli%20soldiers.%20I%20express%20my%20strongest%20condemnation%20of%20these%20shootings%20and%20call%20for%20truth%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20respect%20for%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEmmanuelMacron%2Fstatus%2F1763354898119229476%5C%22%3Ehe%20wrote%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20demanded%20that%20a%20ceasefire%20must%20be%20immediately%20implemented%20to%20allow%20distribution%20of%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20French%20foreign%20minister%20St%C3%A9phane%20S%C3%A9journ%C3%A9%20called%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Flive%2F2024%2Fmar%2F01%2Fgaza-aid-convoy-deaths-israel-middle-east-crisis-live-latest-news%3Fpage%3Dwith%253Ablock-65e195bc8f08a1a184508922%23block-65e195bc8f08a1a184508922%5C%22%3Eindependent%20probe%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CFrance%20calls%20things%20by%20their%20name.%20This%20applies%20when%20we%20designate%20Hamas%20as%20a%20terrorist%20group%2C%20but%20we%20must%20also%20call%20things%20by%20their%20name%20when%20there%20are%20atrocities%20in%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20close%20ally%20of%20Israel%2C%20German%20foreign%20minister%20Annalena%20Baerbock%20wrote%20that%20Israeli%20army%20had%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20explain%20how%20the%20mass%20panic%20and%20shooting%20could%20have%20happened%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20wanted%20relief%20supplies%20for%20themselves%20and%20their%20families%20and%20ended%20up%20dead.%20The%20reports%20from%20Gaza%20shock%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExpressing%20horror%20at%20%E2%80%9Cyet%20another%20carnage%20among%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20desperate%20for%20humanitarian%20aid%E2%80%9D%2C%20EU%20foreign%20minister%20Josef%20Borrell%20Fonteles%20said%20that%20depriving%20people%20of%20food%20aid%20constitutes%20a%20serious%20violation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FJosepBorrellF%2Fstatus%2F1763331544045994157%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Einternational%20humanitarian%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20region%2C%20there%20was%20strong%20condemnation%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20Kuwait%20and%20Qatar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F29%2Fpolitics%2Fbiden-gaza-incidents-ceasefire-talks%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ecompeting%20versions%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20incident%20and%20warned%20that%20the%20deaths%20would%20complicate%20the%20negotiations%20for%20release%20of%20hostages%20and%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20urgent%20meeting%20held%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20discussed%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20killings%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Palestinian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Riyad%20Mansour%2C%20the%20US%20blocked%20the%20issuing%20of%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20Council%2C%20arguing%20that%20there%20were%20contradictory%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intensity%20of%20the%20international%20outcry%20meant%20that%20India%20did%20not%20have%20much%20choice%20but%20to%20issue%20a%20condemnatory%20statement%2C%20even%20though%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20name%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20deaths%20or%20cite%20Israel%20by%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20simply%20tweeted%20that%20India%20was%20in%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%E2%80%9D%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20explosion%20in%20a%20Gaza%20hospital%20killed%20hundreds%20two%20weeks%20later%2C%20the%20Indian%20PM%20for%20the%20first%20time%20during%20this%20current%20conflict%20reiterated%20that%20New%20Delhi%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-palestine-authority-president-mahmoud-abbas-call-israel-gaza%5C%22%3Etraditionally%20supported%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-refuses-to-back-landslide-un-general-assembly-call-for-humanitarian-truce-in-gaza%5C%22%3Eabstained%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20voting%20on%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20that%20called%20for%20immediate%20cessation%20of%20violence%20in%20Gaza.%20Less%20than%20two%20months%20later%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-votes-in-favour-of-unga-resolution-calling-for-immediate-ceasefire-in-gaza%5C%22%3Evoted%20in%20favour%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20new%20resolution%20adopted%20by%20UNGA%20that%20called%20for%20an%20urgent%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709315293000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F28144318%2Fhumanitarian-aid-to-gaza-e1701163097133.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdeeply-shocked-india-on-palestinians