C%22752%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01181848%2Fimage-1890.png%20752w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01181848%2Fimage-1890-300x81.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699682%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22202%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20the%20money%20taken%20from%20Hindu%20temples%20by%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20being%20diverted%20to%20the%20welfare%20of%20minority%20communities%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnataka%20government%E2%80%99s%20Muzrai%20minister%20Ramalinga%20Reddy%2C%20responding%20to%20BJP%20MP%20Tejasvi%20Surya%E2%80%99s%20allegations%2C%20tweeted%20that%20Muzrai%20department%20money%20could%20be%20used%20only%20on%20temples%20and%20minority%20welfare%20department%20money%20could%20only%20be%20used%20on%20minority%20buildings%20and%20religious%20places.%20He%20insisted%20no%20money%20from%20the%20temples%20had%20been%20given%20to%20the%20minority%20welfare%20department.%20Along%20with%20this%2C%20the%20Muzrai%20minister%20called%20the%20viral%20claim%20false%20and%20said%20that%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20members%20were%20experts%20in%20misleading%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBJP4India%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40BJP4India%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTejasvi_Surya%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40Tejasvi_Surya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Money%20from%20the%20endowment%20department%20can%20only%20be%20used%20on%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Money%20from%20the%20minority%20welfare%20department%20can%20only%20be%20used%20on%20minority%20buildings%20and%20religious%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20No%20money%20from%20temples%20has%20been%20given%20to%20the%20minority%20welfare%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FpPje3vb5m1%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FpPje3vb5m1%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ramalinga%20Reddy%20(%40RLR_BTM)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRLR_BTM%2Fstatus%2F1758425817514914303%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2016%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20news%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fkarnataka%2Fan-editor-gave-the-karnataka-budget-a-communal-spin-but-heres-what-the-numbers-say%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Reddy%20stated%20that%20the%20government%20had%20no%20control%20over%20the%20temples.%20He%20explained%20that%20budget%20funds%20allocated%20for%20the%20Muzrai%20Department%20since%202011%20were%20entirely%20utilised%20for%20the%20development%20of%20all%20categories%20of%20temples%20falling%20under%20it.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20amount%20allocated%20in%20the%20budget%20for%20the%20Minority%20Welfare%20Department%20was%20used%20solely%20for%20religious%20and%20cultural%20welfare%20activities%20of%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAlt%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%20contacted%20Rajendra%20Kataria%2C%20the%20principal%20secretary%20to%20the%20Karnataka%20government%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20department%2C%20for%20more%20information.%20He%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20about%2035%2C000%20temples%20under%20the%20Muzrai%20department.%20These%20temples%20are%20divided%20into%20A%2C%20B%20and%20C%20categories%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20income%20and%20property.%20Temples%20with%20incomes%20more%20than%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20are%20Category%20A%2C%20with%20a%20total%20of%20205%20temples.%20Temples%20with%20incomes%20ranging%20from%20Rs%205%20to%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20are%20categorised%20under%20the%20B%20category%2C%20consisting%20of%20193%20temples.%20Finally%2C%20those%20generating%20an%20income%20less%20than%20Rs%205%20lakh%20are%20placed%20in%20the%20C%20category%2C%20making%20up%2034%2C165%20temples.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20take%20money%20from%20these%20temples.%20Money%20from%20the%20donation%20boxes%20(Hundi)%20is%20drawn%20by%20the%20local%20committees%20and%20deposited%20in%20the%20bank%20accounts%20of%20the%20respective%20temples%2C%20which%20is%20used%20by%20the%20temples%20for%20their%20management%2C%20organising%20programs%2C%20development%20of%20the%20temple%2C%20etc.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBigger%20temples%20have%20a%20local%20official%20in%20whose%20presence%20the%20donation%20box%20is%20opened%20by%20the%20committee%20and%20this%20money%20is%20deposited%20in%20his%20account%20only.%20This%20money%20does%20not%20go%20to%20the%20government.%20The%20work%20of%20the%20Muzrai%20department%20of%20the%20government%20is%20to%20provide%20financial%20assistance%20to%20these%20temples%20for%20their%20development.%20The%20government%20also%20makes%20arrangements%20for%20the%20convenience%20of%20devotees%2C%20such%20as%20the%20opening%20of%20guest%20houses%20for%20pilgrims.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20religious%20sites%20like%20Tirupati%2C%20Varanasi%2C%20Srisailam%2C%20Mantralayam%2C%20and%20Tuljapur.%20Misinformation%20is%20being%20spread%20on%20social%20media%20that%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20takes%20money%20from%20Hindu%20temples%20and%20uses%20it%20to%20fund%20religious%20institutions%20of%20non-Hindu%20religions.%20A%20meeting%20of%20the%20Muzrai%20department%20has%20been%20held%20regarding%20this%20issue%20and%20appropriate%20action%20will%20be%20taken%20against%20those%20spreading%20such%20rumours.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20working%20in%20the%20government%20of%20Karnataka%20sent%20us%20a%20note%20on%20the%20Amendment%20Bill%20of%20Karnataka%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20and%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Act%201997.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.altnews.in%2Fs%2FYqRTKiaMfiTQp5a%5C%22%3EComplete%20file%3C%2Fa%3E)%20This%20note%20explains%20the%20changes%20related%20and%20their%20purpose.%20It%20is%20clearly%20written%20in%20Point%206%20of%20this%20note%20that%20the%20Archakas%20and%20temple%20employees%20of%20these%20temples%20needed%20more%20money%20to%20meet%20the%20demands%20of%20economically%20backward%20C%20grade%20institutions%20under%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund.%20Therefore%2C%20from%20this%20point%20of%20view%2C%20it%20was%20considered%20necessary%20to%20revise%20this%20amount.%20This%20amount%20would%20be%20used%20only%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20C%20Group%20temples%20along%20with%20the%20Archaks%20and%20employees%20of%20the%20temples.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20note%20has%20a%20list%20of%20facilities%20to%20be%20provided%20to%20the%20temple%20employees%20and%20Archaks%20under%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund.%20For%20example%2C%20scholarship%20to%20the%20children%20of%20Archaks%2C%20insurance%20to%20the%20temple%20employees%2C%20accommodation%20facilities%2C%20free%20trips%20to%20Kashi%20and%20South%20India%20for%20the%20families%20of%20the%20temple%20employees%2C%20a%20central%20information%20center%20for%20the%20devotees%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20clearly%20stated%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20this%20note%20that%20since%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20Act%20in%202003%2C%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund%20has%20been%20used%20only%20for%20Hindu%20religious%20institutions%20and%20would%20be%20used%20only%20for%20them%20in%20the%20future.%20It%20has%20not%20been%20used%20for%20any%20other%20purpose%20or%20for%20people%20of%20other%20religions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01182112%2Fimage-1891.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22737%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01182112%2Fimage-1891.p